    "guides.bookGoal": "Price the whole cost, not the headline.",
    "guides.bookBody": "A luxury quotation is a stack of lines, and only the first of them is the apartment. Ask for the complete cost sheet with every charge named — preferential location, parking, club membership, maintenance security, statutory taxes, stamp duty and registration — and compare offers on total outlay rather than on the per sq.ft figure. Then compare payment plans the same way: a construction-linked schedule and a down-payment schedule rarely cost the same amount for the same home.",
