    "guides.agreementBody": "The brochure is marketing; the agreement for sale is the contract. Everything you were told at the sales desk is worth precisely as much as its equivalent clause. Have the draft read by your own advocate, not the developer's, and treat any refusal to share the draft before booking as information in itself. Register the agreement and pay the stamp duty — an unregistered agreement is a weak instrument in a dispute.",
