    "overview.crumb": "Overview",
    "overview.eyebrow": "M3M Brabus Overview",
    "overview.title": "A limited collection,",
    "overview.accent": "engineered with BRABUS.",
    "overview.ledeOf": "of",
    "overview.ledeAt": "at",
    "overview.ledeOnRoad": ", on Golf Course Extension Road. What follows is the case for the project — and the record of what",
    "overview.ledeTail": "has published about it, and what it has not.",
    "overview.imgAlt": "M3M Brabus — the tower",
    "overview.towerCaption": "The Tower",
    "overview.briefKicker": "The project, in brief",
    "overview.briefTitle1": "A branded residence,",
    "overview.briefTitle2": "in the truest sense.",
    "overview.briefP1a": "is developed by",
    "overview.briefP1b": "and shaped by the ethos of",
    "overview.briefP1c": "— the German marque that built its name rebuilding finished motor cars to a specification the factory never offered. The influence is meant to be felt in the specification rather than read off a badge: bespoke, obsessive, made once.",
    "overview.briefP2a": "It is written for a narrow readership — families who already own well and are buying a last address rather than a next one, and principals who want the home to read the way the car in the porch does. Consider it if you value provenance over frontage: an",
    "overview.briefP2b": "address, a global marque's discipline carried into the interiors, a floor plate large enough to live at villa scale without leaving the skyline, and security and concierge that keep no office hours.",
    "overview.apartKicker": "What sets it apart",
    "overview.ctaTitle": "See it",
