    "masterplan.eyebrow": "M3M Brabus Master Plan",
    "masterplan.title": "The drawing that decides",
    "masterplan.accent": "everything after it.",
    "masterplan.lede": "M3M India has not released a site layout for M3M Brabus. Rather than publish an invented one, this page teaches you to read the real thing — and gets you the document itself the moment it can be shared.",
    "masterplan.readKicker": "Reading a master plan",
    "masterplan.readP1": "A master plan is the only drawing that describes the thing you cannot change after possession. A kitchen can be refitted and a wall can be moved; the distance between your window and the tower opposite is fixed the day the layout is sanctioned. It is also the drawing buyers spend the least time with, because it is the least photogenic — a floor plan shows a home, a render shows a mood, and a master plan shows geometry.",
    "masterplan.readP2": "Learn to read it and the rest of the sales conversation changes. You stop asking how many amenities there are and start asking where they sit. You stop accepting “three sides open” as a specification and start checking whether the spacing makes it true. Seven layers are worth your attention, in this order.",
    "masterplan.svgAria": "Schematic diagram illustrating general master-plan principles: a site boundary with a north point, staggered tower footprints with spacing marked between them, one footprint shown open on three faces, a central amenity core, and a service route kept separate from resident movement. Not the site plan of this project.",
