    "gallery.eyebrow": "M3M Brabus Gallery",
    "gallery.title": "The published set,",
    "gallery.accent": "in full.",
    "gallery.ledeA": "Three official renders exist for",
    "gallery.ledeB": "— the towers at dusk, the arrival court and the marble lobby. All three are hung here, at size and under accurate captions. Nothing else has been released, and nothing else is invented to fill the wall.",
    "gallery.rendersKicker": "The official renders",
    "gallery.platesComplete": "plates · the complete set",
    "gallery.enlarge": "Enlarge",
    "gallery.plate": "Plate",
    "gallery.creditRender": "Official render by",
    "gallery.creditArtist": "Artist's impression, indicative of design intent and subject to the approved plan",
    "gallery.creditArtistShort": "Artist's impression",
    "gallery.plate1Name": "The Towers",
    "gallery.plate1Subject": "Architecture · at dusk",
    "gallery.plate1Lede": "The silhouette on the Golf Course Extension skyline.",
    "gallery.plate1Body": "The towers at dusk, seen across the landscaped grounds — the only published view of the building in its setting, and the one worth the longest look. Massing, the ratio of glass to solid, and the way the base meets the ground are all settled at this scale and cannot be retrofitted afterwards. Read it as an elevation study rather than a census: no tower count, floor count or land area has been released, and this render asserts none of them.",
    "gallery.plate1Alt": "Official M3M Brabus render — the towers at dusk above the landscaped grounds, Sector 58, Gurgaon",
    "gallery.plate2Name": "The Arrival",
    "gallery.plate2Subject": "Approach · the porte-cochère",
    "gallery.plate2Lede": "The approach a car makes to the door, and the first room a guest stands in.",
    "gallery.plate2Body": "The arrival court: a marble wall, a water court and a canopy proportioned for stepping out of a car rather than walking up to a door. Arrival is the part of a branded residence hardest to correct later and easiest to judge early — where the car stops, where it goes afterwards, and how much building you pass through before the lift. This is the render that shows it.",
    "gallery.plate2Alt": "Official M3M Brabus render — the porte-cochère arrival court with marble wall and water court, Sector 58, Gurgaon",
    "gallery.plate3Name": "The Lobby",
    "gallery.plate3Subject": "Interior · double height",
    "gallery.plate3Lede": "Marble, brass light and the marque, stated once at the door.",
    "gallery.plate3Body": "The double-height lobby and its lounge — stone underfoot, brass in the light fittings, and the marque set once at the entrance rather than repeated down the room. This is the only interior M3M has released. The residences, the club, the spa and the pool have no published photography at all, which is why you will not find them hung further down this page.",
    "gallery.plate3Alt": "Official M3M Brabus render — the double-height marble lobby and lounge, Sector 58, Gurgaon",
    "gallery.absentKicker": "What is not here, and why",
    "gallery.absentIntroA": "A gallery is only worth reading if every caption is true. Where",
    "gallery.absentIntroB": "has released no image, this page shows none — rather than repeating one of the three above under the name of a room it does not depict. Here is the rest of the material, the status it is genuinely at, and the page that already handles it properly without a picture.",
    "gallery.absentInteriorsT": "Residence interiors",
    "gallery.absentInteriorsS": "No render released",
    "gallery.absentInteriorsD": "No published view of a living room, a bedroom or a kitchen exists. The layouts themselves are drawn as indicative zone plans on the floor plans page; the dimensioned sheets come from the client team.",
    "gallery.labelFloorPlans": "Floor plans",
    "gallery.absentClubT": "Club, spa, pool & gym",
    "gallery.absentClubS": "No photography released",
    "gallery.absentClubD": "Every facility named across the official listing is set out in full on the amenities page, in type rather than in borrowed pictures of somebody else's clubhouse.",
    "gallery.labelAmenities": "Amenities",
    "gallery.absentMasterT": "The master plan",
    "gallery.absentMasterS": "On request",
    "gallery.absentMasterD": "No site layout has been released, so none is reproduced. The master plan page teaches you to read the real drawing and requests it on your behalf.",
    "gallery.labelMasterPlan": "Master plan",
    "gallery.absentSiteT": "Site progress photography",
    "gallery.absentSiteS": "None held",
    "gallery.absentSiteD": "We hold no dated site photography and no verified progress figure. The construction status page states the position as it stands and shows you how to check it yourself.",
    "gallery.labelConstruction": "Construction status",
    "gallery.imageryOnRequest": "Imagery on request",
    "gallery.restSharedA": "The rest is shared",
    "gallery.restSharedB": "privately, as it lands.",
    "gallery.requestBody": "Interior renders, amenity visuals, the dimensioned floor-plan sheets and the master plan are released to the private client team ahead of the public site. Register once and you receive each of them as it is authorised — dated, attributed, and with its approval status stated plainly rather than smoothed over.",
